SIMPLE: slant
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Slant
<hw>Slant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Slanted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Slanting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>slenten</ets> to
slope, slide; cf. Sw. <ets>slinta</ets> to slide.]</ety> <def>To be
turned or inclined from a right line or level; to lie obliquely; to
slope.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>On the side of younder <qex>slanting</qex> hill.</q>
<rj><qau>Dodsley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slant</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Slant
<hw>Slant</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To turn from a direct line; to
give an oblique or sloping direction to; <as>as, to <ex>slant</ex> a
line</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slant</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Slant
<hw>Slant</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A slanting direction or
plane; a slope; <as>as, it lies on a <ex>slant</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An oblique reflection or gibe; a sarcastic
remark.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Slant or wind</b></col>, <cd>a local variation of the
wind from its general direction.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slant</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Slant
<hw>Slant</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. dial. Sw. <ets>slant</ets>. See
<er>Slant</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos>]</ety> <def>Inclined from a direct
line, whether horizontal or perpendicular; sloping; oblique.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>slant</xex> lightning.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slanting</ent>⟦br⟧
